# MediQuery-X Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
MediQuery-X is a healthcare RAG chatbot using LangGraph, FastAPI, Pinecone, and Groq.
It answers medical FAQs with multi-step reasoning, HIPAA-conscious design, and semantic search.

## Stack
- Backend: FastAPI (Python 3.11)
- Orchestration: LangGraph (multi-node reasoning graph)
- Vector DB: Pinecone
- LLM: Groq (llama3-70b-8192)
- Embeddings: HuggingFace sentence-transformers
- Frontend: Streamlit
- Containerization: Docker + docker-compose

## Code Style
- Use Python type hints everywhere
- Pydantic v2 for all request/response models
- Async functions for all FastAPI routes and LangGraph nodes
- Keep each LangGraph node focused on ONE responsibility
- Use environment variables for all secrets (never hardcode)
- Add docstrings to all classes and functions

## LangGraph Conventions
- State is always a TypedDict
- Nodes are async functions: async def node_name(state: GraphState) -> GraphState
- Edges are defined after all nodes
- Graph is compiled once at startup and reused

## File Structure
- backend/app/api/        → FastAPI route handlers
- backend/app/core/       → config, graph definition, state
- backend/app/services/   → pinecone, groq, embedding services
- backend/app/models/     → pydantic request/response schemas
- frontend/               → streamlit app
- scripts/                → data ingestion scripts

## Error Handling
- All service calls wrapped in try/except
- Return structured error responses from API
- Log errors with context (never swallow silently)
